# Midasbuy Redeem API

HTTP API for redeeming Midasbuy codes and looking up player info. All
endpoints are `POST`, expect `application/json` request bodies (up to 16 KB)
and are authenticated with the `x-key` header.

- **Base URL** — `http://<your-server>:8000`
- **Auth** — header `x-key: <api-key>`
- **Content** — `application/json`

> The `x-key` is issued via the Telegram bot (`/accept <user_id> <days>`).
> The same bot is used to set the Midasbuy cookies that the API will use.

## Endpoints overview

| Method | Path        | Purpose                              |
| ------ | ----------- | ------------------------------------ |
| POST   | `/redeem`   | Redeem a code on a player account    |
| POST   | `/info`     | Look up player info by `player_id`   |
| POST   | `/stats`    | Usage counters and remaining quota   |
| POST   | `/history`  | Recent redeem attempts               |

Any other method or unknown path returns `404 {"detail":"error"}`.

## Authentication

Every request must include:

```
x-key: <api-key>
```

A missing, unknown or expired key returns `401 {"detail":"error"}`. Details
are omitted on purpose. After 10 consecutive `401` responses from the same
IP the IP is banned for one hour.

## Rate limits

| Limit                    | Scope        | Window               |
| ------------------------ | ------------ | -------------------- |
| 5 requests / minute      | per API key  | 60 s                 |
| 1000 redemptions / day   | per API key  | resets 00:00 MSK     |
| 30 requests / minute     | per IP       | 60 s                 |
| 10 concurrent `/redeem`  | server-wide  | —                    |

A quota violation returns HTTP `429`. The first violation wins — checks run
in this order: per-IP rate → key auth → per-key 5/min → daily 1000 →
concurrency.

## Localization

The `message` field in responses follows the language the key owner picked
in the Telegram bot (Russian or English). Other fields (status codes, field
names, `/stats` and `/history` payloads) are language-independent. Changing
the language in the bot takes effect on the very next API call.

---

## `POST /redeem`

Redeem a Midasbuy code on the given player account.

### Request body

| Field       | Type   | Required | Description                |
| ----------- | ------ | -------- | -------------------------- |
| `player_id` | string | yes      | Numeric Midasbuy player ID |
| `code`      | string | yes      | Redeem code as printed     |

### Example

```bash
curl -X POST http://<your-server>:8000/redeem \
  -H "x-key: <api-key>" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"player_id":"51569444543","code":"Grmndgic2f2272H8be"}'
```

### Success — HTTP 200

```json
{
  "success":  true,
  "message":  "Код успешно активирован — товар зачислен на аккаунт",
  "nickname": "GNCOD"
}
```

### Failure — HTTP 200, `success: false`

```json
{ "success": false, "message": "<localized error text>" }
```

| Reason                 | RU                                                                                  | EN                                                                                |
| ---------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| invalid code           | Код недействителен. Проверьте правильность ввода                                    | Code is invalid. Please check the value and try again                             |
| already used           | Этот код уже был активирован ранее                                                  | This code has already been redeemed                                               |
| expired                | Срок действия кода истёк, активация больше недоступна                               | Code has expired and can no longer be redeemed                                    |
| player not found       | Игрок с таким ID не найден. Проверьте Player ID и попробуйте снова                  | Player with this ID was not found. Check the Player ID and try again              |
| authorization outdated | Авторизация Midasbuy устарела. Обратитесь к администратору для обновления           | Midasbuy authorization is outdated. Please contact the administrator              |
| generic failure        | Не удалось активировать код. Попробуйте позже или обратитесь к администратору       | Failed to redeem the code. Try again later or contact the administrator           |

### Quota — HTTP 429

| Reason             | RU                                                                                       | EN                                                                       |
| ------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| per-key 5/min      | Слишком много запросов. Лимит: 5 в минуту. Подождите немного                             | Too many requests. Limit: 5 per minute. Please slow down                 |
| daily 1000         | Достигнут суточный лимит активаций (1000 в сутки). Счётчик обнулится в 00:00 по МСК      | Daily redeem limit reached (1000 per day). Counter resets at 00:00 MSK   |
| server overloaded  | Сервер сейчас перегружен. Повторите запрос через несколько секунд                        | Server is currently overloaded. Please retry in a few seconds            |

### Bad request — HTTP 400

| RU                                                  | EN                                              |
| --------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------- |
| В теле запроса должны быть поля player_id и code    | Request body must contain `player_id` and `code` |

---

## `POST /info`

Look up player info on Midasbuy by `player_id`.

### Request body

| Field       | Type   | Required | Description                |
| ----------- | ------ | -------- | -------------------------- |
| `player_id` | string | yes      | Numeric Midasbuy player ID |

### Example

```bash
curl -X POST http://<your-server>:8000/info \
  -H "x-key: <api-key>" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"player_id":"51569444543"}'
```

### Success — HTTP 200

```json
{
  "success":   true,
  "player_id": "51569444543",
  "nickname":  "GNCOD",
  "zone_id":   "1",
  "is_ban":    false
}
```

### Failure — HTTP 200, `success: false`

| Reason                 | RU                                                                            | EN                                                                  |
| ---------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| player not found       | Игрок с таким ID не найден. Проверьте Player ID и попробуйте снова            | Player with this ID was not found. Check the Player ID and try again |
| authorization outdated | Авторизация Midasbuy устарела. Обратитесь к администратору для обновления     | Midasbuy authorization is outdated. Please contact the administrator |
| generic failure        | Не удалось получить информацию об игроке. Попробуйте позже                    | Failed to retrieve player info. Please try again later              |

### Bad request — HTTP 400

| RU                                              | EN                                          |
| ----------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------- |
| В теле запроса должно быть поле player_id       | Request body must contain `player_id`        |

---

## `POST /stats`

Returns usage counters and remaining quota for the current API key. The
payload is language-independent.

### Request body

```json
{}
```

### Example

```bash
curl -X POST http://<your-server>:8000/stats \
  -H "x-key: <api-key>" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{}'
```

### Response — HTTP 200

```json
{
  "success": true,

  "key": {
    "expires_at":     1782384336,
    "expires_at_iso": "2026-06-25 10:45:36",
    "ttl_seconds":    2590409
  },

  "rate_limit_minute": {
    "max":            5,
    "used":           1,
    "remaining":      4,
    "window_seconds": 60
  },

  "daily_redeem": {
    "limit":            1000,
    "used":             2,
    "remaining":        998,
    "reset_at":         1779829200,
    "reset_at_msk":     "2026-05-27 00:00:00 MSK",
    "reset_in_seconds": 35273,
    "timezone":         "MSK (UTC+3)"
  },

  "totals": {
    "success":  1,
    "fail":     1,
    "all_time": 2
  }
}
```

### Field reference

| Field                            | Description                                  |
| -------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------- |
| `key.expires_at`                 | unix timestamp of subscription end           |
| `key.ttl_seconds`                | seconds until the subscription expires       |
| `rate_limit_minute.used`         | requests made in the current 60-second window |
| `rate_limit_minute.remaining`    | requests still allowed in the current window |
| `daily_redeem.used`              | `/redeem` calls made today (MSK day)         |
| `daily_redeem.remaining`         | `/redeem` calls left today                   |
| `daily_redeem.reset_at`          | unix timestamp of the next 00:00 MSK         |
| `daily_redeem.reset_in_seconds`  | seconds until the daily counter resets       |
| `totals`                         | lifetime success / fail counts for this key  |

---

## `POST /history`

Recent `/redeem` attempts for the current API key, newest first.

### Request body

| Field   | Type    | Required | Description                |
| ------- | ------- | -------- | -------------------------- |
| `limit` | integer | no       | `1..500`, default `50`     |

### Example

```bash
curl -X POST http://<your-server>:8000/history \
  -H "x-key: <api-key>" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"limit":3}'
```

### Response — HTTP 200

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "count":   2,
  "items": [
    {
      "created_at":     1779792974,
      "created_at_iso": "2026-05-26 10:56:14",
      "player_id":      "51889127192",
      "code":           "Grmndgic2f2272H8be",
      "success":        true
    },
    {
      "created_at":     1779792461,
      "created_at_iso": "2026-05-26 10:47:41",
      "player_id":      "51569444543",
      "code":           "Grmndgic2f2272H8be",
      "success":        false
    }
  ]
}
```

---

## Status codes

| Code | Meaning                                                                                              |
| ---- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| 200  | Request processed. Check `success` in the body for the actual outcome of `/redeem` and `/info`.       |
| 400  | Validation error. Body returns `success: false` and a localized `message`.                            |
| 401  | Authentication failed. Body is `{"detail":"error"}`. Details are omitted on purpose.                  |
| 404  | Unknown endpoint or wrong method. Body is `{"detail":"error"}`.                                       |
| 429  | Quota / limit exceeded. For key-level limits the body is localized; for IP limits — `{"detail":"error"}`. |
| 500  | Server-side error. Should not happen in normal operation.                                             |

## Notes

- All endpoints are `POST`. `GET`, `PUT`, `DELETE` return `404`.
- JSON body must be valid and not exceed 16 KB.
- Timestamps in `*_iso` fields without an explicit `MSK` suffix are UTC.
- The locale for `message` follows the Telegram-bot setting of the key
  owner. It is changed via `/start` → profile → Russian / English.
